                <head>To the Editors of the Staunton Spectator</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Very Respectfully, THE PROPRIETOR</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Letter about the travelers stuck on the train during the 1/18/57 snowstorm.
                    The travelers stayed at his hotel or tavern, and he takes issue with their
                    descriptions of it, and of him. He answers the first writer's complaints about
                    food, service and accomodations one by one.</summary>
            </div>
