        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1857.03.18.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Slavery in Virginia</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>When was it ever known that Northern men emigrating to the South failed to
                    become the most fiery champions of slavery?</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Discusses reports from the Petersburg Express and the Charleston Mercury
                    about the number of slave in VA, and the continiuing viability of the
                    institution there. Mercury believes that the Deep South can't "rely" on the
                    border states to resist abolition. Also notes a report in the New York Herald
                    that Northerners are about to make a xconcerted effort to abolitionize VA. SS
                    wants to disbelieve it, but just isn't sure. Ultimately, isn't worried baout
                    abolition (see p)</summary>
            </div>
